-final-security\",children:[\"Pattern 3: Use Layouts and Pages for UI Decisions, Not Final Security\",(0,n.jsx)(e.a,{className:\"anchor-link\",\"aria-label\":\"Link to section\",href:\"#pattern-3-use-layouts-and-pages-for-ui-decisions-not-final-security\",children:\"#\"})]}),`\n`,(0,n.jsx)(e.p,{children:\"Layouts are good at shaping user experience.\"}),`\n`,(0,n.jsx)(e.p,{children:\"They are not enough by themselves to secure the system.\"}),`\n`,(0,n.jsx)(e.p,{children:\"For example, a dashboard layout can fetch the current user, select a nav variant, or redirect an unauthenticated visitor early. That is helpful. But if the same user can still hit a Route Handler or trigger a Server Action that does not re-check permissions, the system is still incomplete.\"}),`\n`,(0,n.jsx)(e.p,{children:\"This is where many apps start to feel flaky. The UI looks protected, but the server contract is weaker than the shell around it.\"}),`\n`,(0,n.jsx)(a,{leftTitle:\"Fragile pattern\",rightTitle:\"Scalable pattern\",left:[\"Protect the page shell and assume the rest is covered\",\"Use Proxy redirects for role logic on every request\",\"Let layout checks stand in for mutation security\",\"Treat navigation control as the full authorization model\"],right:[\"Use layouts for user experience and early branching\",\"Keep Proxy focused on optimistic route gating\",\"Re-check permissions inside Route Handlers and Server Actions\",\"Treat data access as the final authority\"]}),`\n`,(0,n.jsxs)(e.h2,{id:\"the-anti-patterns-that-age-badly\",children:[\"The Anti-Patterns That Age Badly\",(0,n.jsx)(e.a,{className:\"anchor-link\",\"aria-label\":\"Link to section\",href:\"#the-anti-patterns-that-age-badly\",children:\"#\"})]}),`\n`,(0,n.jsx)(e.p,{children:\"There are a few patterns that look reasonable in week one and become painful in month six.\"}),`\n`,(0,n.jsxs)(e.h3,{id:\"doing-database-or-revocation-checks-in-proxy\",children:[\"Doing database or revocation checks in Proxy\",(0,n.jsx)(e.a,