 decisions that really belong to your secure server layer.\"}),`\n`,(0,n.jsx)(e.p,{children:\"That is where you see symptoms such as:\"}),`\n`,(0,n.jsxs)(e.ul,{children:[`\n`,(0,n.jsx)(e.li,{children:\"content flashes before a redirect settles\"}),`\n`,(0,n.jsx)(e.li,{children:\"redirect loops between public and private routes\"}),`\n`,(0,n.jsx)(e.li,{children:\"behavior that differs between hard refresh and client navigation\"}),`\n`]}),`\n`,(0,n.jsx)(e.p,{children:\"A safer rule is this:\"}),`\n`,(0,n.jsxs)(e.ul,{children:[`\n`,(0,n.jsx)(e.li,{children:\"use Proxy redirects for missing or obviously invalid sessions\"}),`\n`,(0,n.jsx)(e.li,{children:\"use server-side data checks for permissions, ownership, and resource-specific access\"}),`\n`,(0,n.jsxs)(e.li,{children:[\"use \",(0,n.jsx)(e.code,{children:\"redirect()\"}),\" or \",(0,n.jsx)(e.code,{children:\"notFound()\"}),\" from the server layer once you know the real business decision\"]}),`\n`]}),`\n`,(0,n.jsxs)(e.h3,{id:\"matching-too-broadly\",children:[\"Matching too broadly\",(0,n.jsx)(e.a,{className:\"anchor-link\",\"aria-label\":\"Link to section\",href:\"#matching-too-broadly\",children:\"#\"})]}),`\n`,(0,n.jsx)(e.p,{children:\"If your matcher includes assets, images, or routes that do not need guarding, you pay for work that produces no security value.\"}),`\n`,(0,n.jsx)(e.p,{children:\"Even a cheap Proxy becomes expensive when it runs unnecessarily across the whole request surface.\"}),`\n`,(0,n.jsxs)(e.h2,{id:\"a-practical-architecture-for-real-apps\",children:[\"A Practical Architecture For Real Apps\",(0,n.jsx)(e.a,{className:\"anchor-link\",\"aria-label\":\"Link to section\",href:\"#a-practical-architecture-for-real-apps\",children:\"#\"})]}),`\n`,(0,n.jsx)(e.p,{children:\"If I were setting up authorization in a fresh Next.js 16 App Router project today, I would use this split:\"}),`\n`,(0,n.jsxs)(t,{children:[(0,n.jsx)(i,{number:\"01\",title:\"Proxy for perimeter control\",children:(0,n.jsx)(e.p,{children:`Check whether a session cookie exists, keep the matcher narrow, and redirect obvious\nunauthenticated traffic away from protected routes.`})}),(0,n.jsx)(i,{number:\"02\",title:\"DAL for secure session verification\",children:(0,n.jsx)(e.p,{children:`Centralize session validation, role lookups, team membership, and ownership checks in\nserver-only code close to the database.`})}),(0,n.jsx)(i,{number:\"03\",title:\"Layouts and pages for experience\",children:(0,n.jsx)(e.p,{children:`Use server-rendered layouts to branch the interface, show the right shell, and improve the feel\nof protected navigation without making them your only security layer.`})}),(0,n.jsx)(i,{number:\"04\",title:\"Handlers and actions for final enforcement\",children:(0,n.jsx)(e.p,{children:`Every sensitive mutation and every sensitive resource read should verify session and\nauthorization again where the work actually happens.`})})]}),`\n`,(0,n.jsx)(e.p,{children:\"This structure is slightly more repetitive than the \\u201Cdo it all in middleware\\u201D tutorial version.\"}),`\n`,(0,n.jsx)(e.p,{children:\"It is also much easier to audit, test, and evolve.\"}),`\n`,(0,n.jsxs)(e.h2,{id:\"the-core-idea-to-keep\",children:[\"The Core Idea To Keep\",(0,n.jsx)(e.a,{className:\"anchor-link\",\"aria-label\":\"Link to section\",href:\"#the-core-idea-to-keep\",children:\"#\"})]}),`\n`,(0,n.jsx)(e.p,{children:\"The biggest mistake is not choosing the wrong helper function. It is assigning the wrong responsibility to the wrong layer.\"}),`\n`,(0,n.jsx)(e.p,{children:\"Proxy is excellent when you keep it fast and boring.\"}),`\n`,(0,n.jsx)(e.p,{children:\"Authorization becomes robust when the final decision lives next to the data that decision protects.\"}),`\n`,(0,n.jsx)(e.p,{children:\"That is the version that scales: quick perimeter checks up front, secure checks deeper in the stack, and no illusion that redirects alone are the same thing as access control.\"}),`\n`,(0,n.jsxs)(l,{type:\"note\",